00:11:50.430 --> 00:11:54.240
that it's carbon, it's a sigma
bond because it's a single

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:57.600
bond, and then it's carbon
2 s p 2 bonded to a

00:11:57.600 --> 00:11:59.080
hydrogen 1 s orbital.

00:11:59.080 --> 00:12:02.060
All right, so let's take
a look at the carbon

00:12:02.060 --> 00:12:03.660
chlorine bond here.

00:12:03.660 --> 00:12:08.850
Again, carbon is still 2 s p 2,
it's the same carbon atom,

00:12:08.850 --> 00:12:11.420
and it's going to be a sigma
bond because it's a single

00:12:11.420 --> 00:12:14.120
bond, but what about the
chlorine, what atomic orbital

00:12:14.120 --> 00:12:15.890
