00:12:22.730 --> 00:12:26.780
It turns out that it's going
to be the chlorine 3 p z.

00:12:26.780 --> 00:12:29.570
So the reason that it's p is
because we're not hybridizing

00:12:29.570 --> 00:12:32.990
it, and the reason that I
specifically say that it's the

00:12:32.990 --> 00:12:36.760
p z instead of the p x or the
p y, is remember that the

00:12:36.760 --> 00:12:39.960
z-axis, that's our bonding
axis, that's our

00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:41.270
internuclear axis.

00:12:41.270 --> 00:12:44.280
So any time we have a p orbital
that's involved in a

00:12:44.280 --> 00:12:47.510
sigma bond, it has to be the z
orbital because that's the

00:12:47.510 --> 00:12:50.570
only one that has the right
orientation to overlap along

00:12:50.570 --> 00:12:52.090
that z-axis.

00:12:52.090 --> 00:12:55.940
So we're going to say it's
carbon s p 2, and then

00:12:55.940 --> 00:12:57.700
chlorine 3 p z.

00:12:57.700 --> 00:13:02.850
All right, so let's look at the
last bond here, which is a

00:13:02.850 --> 00:13:04.980
