00:14:42.280 --> 00:14:44.780
think about in terms of thinking
about its shape and

00:14:44.780 --> 00:14:45.260
its hybridization.

00:14:45.260 --> 00:14:48.180
Vitamin C is an antoxidant.

00:14:48.180 --> 00:14:50.780
So we might remember that from
when we were talking about

00:14:50.780 --> 00:14:52.040
free radicals.

00:14:52.040 --> 00:14:54.450
Free radicals can cause
oxidative damage.

00:14:54.450 --> 00:14:57.080
These antioxidants, some of
our vitamins, including

00:14:57.080 --> 00:14:59.300
vitamin C are antioxidants.

00:14:59.300 --> 00:15:01.500
So that's something that a lot
of people in the general

00:15:01.500 --> 00:15:04.760
population know if they're
into their health.

00:15:04.760 --> 00:15:07.960
But another really important
thing about ascorbic acid is

00:15:07.960 --> 00:15:10.870
that it's an enzyme cofactor.

00:15:10.870 --> 00:15:15.160
And a cofactor just means that
it's some type of molecule or

00:15:15.160 --> 00:15:18.070
atom, in this case it's a
molecule, that's required by

00:15:18.070 --> 00:15:19.990
an enzyme in order
for the enzyme to

00:15:19.990 --> 00:15:21.670
carry out its chemistry.

00:15:21.670 --> 00:15:24.990
And the chemistry that the
enzymes that vitamin C are a

00:15:24.990 --> 00:15:28.700
cofactor for are responsible
for putting oxygen, o h

00:15:28.700 --> 00:15:32.350
groups, onto collagen molecules
in order to form

00:15:32.350 --> 00:15:35.100
what is the collagen
triple helix.

00:15:35.100 --> 00:15:38.790
And collagen is the main
constituent of bones, of

00:15:38.790 --> 00:15:44.070
joints, of connective tissue,
of many important structural

00:15:44.070 --> 00:15:45.140
parts of our bodies.

00:15:45.140 --> 00:15:47.700
So you can imagine that vitamin
C is very important

00:15:47.700 --> 00:15:49.960
because we need to keep
our collagen intact.

00:15:49.960 --> 00:15:52.460
Collogen is actually one of the
most prevalent proteins in

00:15:52.460 --> 00:15:56.790
our entire body, and it makes up
a large part of our cells.

00:15:56.790 --> 00:15:59.960
So you can imagine if we don't
have collagen that is in this

00:15:59.960 --> 00:16:02.910
triple helix, we're going to run
into some problems. Does

00:16:02.910 --> 00:16:05.430
anyone, or I'm sure many of you
do know, but can someone

00:16:05.430 --> 00:16:07.840
tell me what the name is of
the disease if you have a

00:16:07.840 --> 00:16:09.410
deficiency in vitamin C?

00:16:09.410 --> 00:16:10.560
STUDENT: Scurvy.

00:16:10.560 --> 00:16:12.630
PROFESSOR: Yeah, scurvy.

00:16:12.630 --> 00:16:17.330
So scurvy, most often associated
with ships because

00:16:17.330 --> 00:16:23.400
of the 1500's and 1600's and
1700's when boating technology

00:16:23.400 --> 00:16:27.330
was far above biochemistry
technology, so people could

00:16:27.330 --> 00:16:29.890
make ships and go on these long
journeys, but people did

00:16:29.890 --> 00:16:33.190
not yet understand they needed
to keep certain vitamins in

00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:36.720
their bodies, such as vitamin
C. Maybe also, they didn't

00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:38.690
know about -- well they didn't
even have the structure, so

00:16:38.690 --> 00:16:41.390
they couldn't have realized that
vitamin C is polar and

00:16:41.390 --> 00:16:43.460
won't stay in their bodies for
very long, it will get

00:16:43.460 --> 00:16:45.230
excreted out through
their urine.

00:16:45.230 --> 00:16:47.960
So they were not thinking about
how quickly they could

00:16:47.960 --> 00:16:50.590
run into trouble in the
long sea voyages.

00:16:50.590 --> 00:16:54.360
And I don't know how many of you
had a unit on explorers in

00:16:54.360 --> 00:16:55.610
elementary school --

00:16:55.610 --> 00:16:58.500
I did in fifth grade, and one
that always sticks in my head

00:16:58.500 --> 00:17:02.245
is Magellan's trip around the
world, who led the first fleet

00:17:02.245 --> 00:17:03.790
of ships around the globe.

00:17:03.790 --> 00:17:07.310
What they did not mention to us
in fifth grade was that 90%

00:17:07.310 --> 00:17:10.020
of his men died on
that journey.

00:17:10.020 --> 00:17:14.030
And I understand we were young
kids, I didn't want to know

00:17:14.030 --> 00:17:16.510
that at the time, but it's
interesting and it's really

00:17:16.510 --> 00:17:18.460
important, and the reason
for many of

00:17:18.460 --> 00:17:19.470
these deaths was scurvy.

00:17:19.470 --> 00:17:22.350
And it's totally preventable.

00:17:22.350 --> 00:17:25.420
And, in fact, the cure for
scurvy, which is as simple as

00:17:25.420 --> 00:17:29.970
taking vitamin C in any form,
was known for -- since the

00:17:29.970 --> 00:17:32.930
fifth century people started
figuring this out, but the

00:17:32.930 --> 00:17:36.420
problem was there was so much
false information as well that

00:17:36.420 --> 00:17:39.530
it was not a general practice
on ships to be treating men

00:17:39.530 --> 00:17:42.000
that were suffering with vitamin
C or using it as any

00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:43.790
kind of preventative measure.

00:17:43.790 --> 00:17:45.940
The other somewhat interesting
thing I want to say about

00:17:45.940 --> 00:17:49.040
vitamin C is that it was part
of the first ever published

00:17:49.040 --> 00:17:50.520
clinical study.

00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:53.270
And this was a controlled
clinical study that was done

00:17:53.270 --> 00:17:56.790
in the 1700's, the first one
that's ever been reported, and

00:17:56.790 --> 00:17:59.700
not surprisingly it was done on
a ship and it was done by

00:17:59.700 --> 00:18:02.520
James Lind who was a Scottish
naval surgeon.

00:18:02.520 --> 00:18:05.260
And basically, he took 12 of
his men, so this was not a

00:18:05.260 --> 00:18:08.800
very large clinical study like
they do today, but he took 12

00:18:08.800 --> 00:18:11.680
men that were suffering from
scurvy, and he gave them a

00:18:11.680 --> 00:18:15.300
diet mostly of just carbohydrate
mush, because

00:18:15.300 --> 00:18:17.860
when you have scurvy, one of
the first signs is bleeding

00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:19.540
gums and teeth falling
out, they couldn't

00:18:19.540 --> 00:18:20.580
really eat too much.

00:18:20.580 --> 00:18:22.570
But he supplemented
their diet.

00:18:22.570 --> 00:18:24.550
He put them in pairs of two and

00:18:24.550 --> 00:18:26.980
supplemented with 1 of 6 things.

00:18:26.980 --> 00:18:29.900
So two of them got a
pint of cider a day

00:18:29.900 --> 00:18:31.580
to see if that helped.

00:18:31.580 --> 00:18:35.200
Two of them got half a pint of
seawater -- maybe not the best

00:18:35.200 --> 00:18:36.330
group to be in.

00:18:36.330 --> 00:18:38.490
Even worse group to be in is
two of them got diluted

00:18:38.490 --> 00:18:40.760
sulfuric acid.

00:18:40.760 --> 00:18:43.480
Tuned out that didn't
help so well.

00:18:43.480 --> 00:18:47.630
Other things where some got
spices, not so bad.

00:18:47.630 --> 00:18:50.250
And then two of them actually
got citrus fruit.

00:18:50.250 --> 00:18:53.760
So no big surprise ending to
this clinical study, the

00:18:53.760 --> 00:18:57.580
people with citrus fruit were
completely cured and back to

00:18:57.580 --> 00:19:00.320
duty within a week, and I'm not
sure exactly what happened

00:19:00.320 --> 00:19:02.600
to everyone else, but
let's hope they got

00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:05.170
switched over as well.

00:19:05.170 --> 00:19:07.730
But it's just neat to think
about even back then, people

00:19:07.730 --> 00:19:10.600
were doing these controlled
scientific studies, this was

00:19:10.600 --> 00:19:12.190
one of the first cases.

00:19:12.190 --> 00:19:16.350
Unfortunately, it was another
40 years between this study

00:19:16.350 --> 00:19:19.180
being published and the
British Navy requiring

00:19:19.180 --> 00:19:20.150
supplements of citric acid.

00:19:20.150 --> 00:19:24.320
So, really, we've come a long
way in terms of disseminating

00:19:24.320 --> 00:19:26.740
scientific knowledge to the
community, and that's a really

00:19:26.740 --> 00:19:29.510
important part of being
scientists -- not just making

00:19:29.510 --> 00:19:32.680
these discoveries, but also
passing along, for example, to

00:19:32.680 --> 00:19:36.060
these ships full of people
that need to know it.

00:19:36.060 --> 00:19:38.850
So, in terms of scurvy, we
don't see too much of it

00:19:38.850 --> 00:19:42.230
today, but who should
be concerned about

00:19:42.230 --> 00:19:43.600
suffering from scurvy?

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.700
Do we have to worry about our
cats or dogs at home, are they

00:19:46.700 --> 00:19:49.580
getting enough of their
vegetables and vitamin C?

00:19:49.580 --> 00:19:51.270
It turns out we don't
have to worry.

00:19:51.270 --> 00:19:54.080
Primates are who should
be concerned.

00:19:54.080 --> 00:19:55.820
So we need to be concerned,
other

00:19:55.820 --> 00:19:57.740
primates need to be concerned.

00:19:57.740 --> 00:20:01.120
It turns out that most other
mammals actually biosynthesize

00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:03.870
