00:25:10.810 --> 00:25:15.790
So if you talk about the
symmetry and the hybrid or

00:25:15.790 --> 00:25:18.660
atomic orbitals that contribute,
we're talking

00:25:18.660 --> 00:25:20.390
about the c d oxygen bond.

00:25:20.390 --> 00:25:22.310
So go ahead and look at
your notes and see

00:25:22.310 --> 00:25:24.370
what that bond is.

00:25:24.370 --> 00:25:27.950
We already identified the
hybridization of carbon d, so

00:25:27.950 --> 00:25:30.260
we really just need to think
about the oxygen here.

00:25:30.260 --> 00:26:04.340
All right, let's take
10 more seconds.

00:26:04.340 --> 00:26:07.230
OK, I'll take that, 84%.

00:26:07.230 --> 00:26:10.010
That's not bad.

00:26:10.010 --> 00:26:12.790
So again, we're looking
at a sigma bond here.

00:26:12.790 --> 00:26:15.170
It looks like the one people
got it confused with was

00:26:15.170 --> 00:26:18.660
talking about oxygen
s p 2 versus s p 3.

00:26:18.660 --> 00:26:20.710
Remember, you just need to look
at what it is actually

00:26:20.710 --> 00:26:24.260
bound to, so for carbon d, the
oxygen's bound to two atoms

00:26:24.260 --> 00:26:27.890
plus two lone pairs, so it's
going to be s p 3 hybridized.

00:26:27.890 --> 00:26:32.660
So we'll call this a sigma bond
where we have carbon 2 s

00:26:32.660 --> 00:26:37.960
p, now it's s p 2, and
oxygen 2 s p 3.

00:26:37.960 --> 00:26:41.300
All right, let's take a look
at just one more here.

00:26:41.300 --> 00:26:45.430
So, let's look at the carbon
d bond with carbon e.

00:26:45.430 --> 00:26:48.750
So if we can switch back to the
class notes just to see

00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:51.780
that, though you guys can see
it on your notes as well.

00:26:51.780 --> 00:26:54.300
So in terms of that, we're
talking about a double bond

00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:57.650
now, so we know that we have to
have one sigma bond and one

00:26:57.650 --> 00:27:01.090
pi bond to completely describe
our double bond.

00:27:01.090 --> 00:27:03.220
So for the sigma bond, again,
it's going to be

00:27:03.220 --> 00:27:07.710
carbon 2 s p 2.

00:27:07.710 --> 00:27:09.780
And now we're talking about
the other carbon.

00:27:09.780 --> 00:27:13.660
What is the hybridization
of the other carbon?

00:27:13.660 --> 00:27:14.660
Yup, s p 2.

00:27:14.660 --> 00:27:17.040
So carbon 2 s p 2.

00:27:17.040 --> 00:27:19.420
All right, but we're
not done there.

00:27:19.420 --> 00:27:22.250
We also need to talk
about the pi bond.

00:27:22.250 --> 00:27:26.730
So for the pi bond, we'll talk
about carbon 2 p y, and then

00:27:26.730 --> 00:27:29.110
the second carbon 2 p y.

00:27:29.110 --> 00:27:33.970
All right, so I filled in a few
more in your notes, so you

00:27:33.970 --> 00:27:36.340
can maybe cover those up and
make sure that you get all of

00:27:36.340 --> 00:27:40.330
those correct is a good self
